The paper focuses on improving reinforcement learning models for robot navigation using vision and language grounding. This falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Given the emphasis on reinforcement learning and navigation, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely categories. However, the use of vision and language also suggests cs.CV and cs.CL as possible categories, while the machine learning aspect could also place it in cs.LG.
